commit.message: feat: :sparkles: Implemented react-markdown to display the descriptions better.
fix: :bug: Removed I infront of interfaces and fixed safety checks

fix: :recycle: Fixed interfaces

removed redundant interfaces
fix: :lipstick: See more button only appears when on the chapters view in the manga details page

fix: :lipstick: Fixed bug where footer would appear when reading a manga

Check if footer exists in the read manga page and if so I remove it
fix: :lipstick: Fixed spacing for next and prev buttons when in md view

feat: :sparkles: Finished the read manga page and implemented other changes and safety checks.

Included ./routes/read.$manga.index incase the chapter hid is not valid. Added a check to HomePage to ensure footer is there. When latest updated manga is clicked it take your directly to read updated chapter. Also updated reading page routes. Reading page now has prev and next buttons. Included paging for comic chapters api call.
Merge branch 'manga-details-feature' into read-manga-feature

feat: :sparkles: Redesigned the manga details page and improved safety checks due to errors found in testing.

The manga details page now makes use of a navbar at the bottom of the page to traverse between viewable options such as chapters, details and recommendations. Improved safety checks on the homepage to not render some section if the data is not there. Also changed the skeletons a bit.

fix: :ambulance: Fixed a bug that cuased a reading undefined error.

When loading the Trending cards there was an error where I was reading an undefined value. Implemented a quick fix

feat: :sparkles: Implemented the reading page for a manga.

Set up the routes and display of the first chapter of a selected manga. Also added a function to check if an image exists.
fix: :bug: Moved Skeleton components to folders and improved background colouring
Merge branch 'landing-feature' into manga-details-feature

feat: :sparkles: Included Skeletons for loading

When api is loading there is now a Skeleton instead of saying Not Found.

refactor: :recycle: Improved separation of concerns.

Improved separation of ceoncerns for the Manga Details Page as well as for the Skeleton that is rendered when the api is loading.

feat: :sparkles: Created Manga Details Page and set up dynamic routing along with scroll restoration

Created the page that displays manga details and set up the dynamic routing that will fetch the clicked on manga's data. Also added a loading skeleton. Included scroll restoration as well when using the return arrows. Made use of default not found component to handle not found pages.
style: :bug: Fixed responsiveness of top ten card
style: :bug: Changed cursor to pointer when hovering over a manga
fix: :bug: Changed UpdatedManga to NewUpdatedManga to descibe better what it is

fix: :truck: Renamed plural components to singular. Renamed some of the data definition types

Some files were plural that were not supposed to be, for example "ListLatestUpdates" became "UpdatedManga""

fix: :bug: Completed recommended changes from PR

DId some restructuring and made components that list certain elements instead of doing multiple loops. Fixed the format date function.
fix: :bug: Improve spacing between components to show better separation

fix: :bug: Improved styling and grammar

Removed the shadow of the newest chapter pill and changed Manga to Manhwa and This weeks trending to Trending This Week
fix: :bug: Removed Comments

fix: :bug: Filtered seasonal mangas for safe content

Included a filter to only have "safe" mangas and also made use of a line clamp for titles that are too long.

feat: :sparkles: Added some guard cluases and tweeked the styling.

Finished up the styling and changed how I display the latest updates. Tweeked the date function as well to say how long ago something was updated. Made the navbar fixed to the top when scrolling. Swapped the borders for shadows.

feat: :sparkles: Added a few components to the home page

Finished the touches on top trending manga and added components for latest updates, top ten, and seasonal manga. Also included a format date service. Structured the code better as well.
